Package com.abc.ds.list

Interface DSList<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DSIterable<T>, DSSack<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayDSList
    public interface DSList<T>
extends DSSack<T>
    A sack of references to objects of type T (always ordered and duplicates are allowed). This DSList IS-A DSSack.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      static int NOT_FOUND_INDEX
      Used as an int value to indicate that nothing was found.

      • firstIndexOf

        int firstIndexOf​(T item,
                 int fromIndex)
        Searches forward from the specified fromIndex of the list for the next occurrence of the specified item and, if found, returns the index where it was found. If not found, then NOT_FOUND_INDEX is returned. If fromIndex is less than 0, is it silently increased to 0. If fromIndex is greater than or equal to count, then NOT_FOUND_INDEX is returned.

      • firstIndexOf

        int firstIndexOf​(T item)
        Searches forward from the beginning of the list for the first occurrence of the specified item and, if found, returns the index where it was found. If not found, then NOT_FOUND_INDEX is returned.

      • lastIndexOf

        int lastIndexOf​(T item,
                int fromIndex)
        Searches backward from the specified fromIndex of the list for the next occurrence of the specified item and, if found, returns the index where it was found. If not found, then NOT_FOUND_INDEX is returned. If fromIndex is less than 0, then NOT_FOUND_INDEX is returned. If fromIndex is greater than or equal to count, then it is silently reduced to (count - 1).

      • lastIndexOf

        int lastIndexOf​(T item)
        Searches backward from the end of the list for the first occurrence of the specified item and, if found, returns the index where it was found. If not found, then NOT_FOUND_INDEX is returned.
